He had cut that fever that says, I think the grass is greener on the other side.

17:04.547 --> 17:08.531
Anybody else ever been there with a job, with a marriage, with a family or whatever?

17:08.671 --> 17:10.493
I think the grass is greener on the other side.

17:11.113 --> 17:14.697
Here's a bit of a tip when it comes to that syndrome, that fever.

17:15.217 --> 17:21.403
If you begin to think that the grass is greener on the other side in a marriage, in a business, in a job, or whatever, what are your own grass?

17:23.445 --> 17:28.210
It works because the grass is never greener on

17:28.322 --> 17:29.104
the other side.

17:29.144 --> 17:31.168
But you couldn't tell that to this young little guy.

17:31.188 --> 17:40.188
He saw, he had friends out there that were living life and here he is home with his dad and this, you know, you know, rinky dink house and just hanging out with his brother.

17:40.208 --> 17:41.591
He's like, I want to get out of here.

17:41.631 --> 17:44.818
I want to, I want to break through and, and I want to experience life.

17:44.878 --> 17:48.786
And in some lessons you can only learn by, by tasting them.

17:49.410 --> 17:51.453
and experiencing them, so the dad gives him his money.

17:51.733 --> 17:55.098
He takes his money, Jesus says he goes off and he spends it in wild living.

17:55.118 --> 18:09.277
And when he's almost out of his money, a famine hits the land, so now everybody's out of work, there's no food, and so somehow he manages to talk this farmer into a job, and so the farmer gives him a job feeding pigs out in his field.

18:10.638 --> 18:11.740
Not a very lucrative job.

18:12.781 --> 18:19.410
And so one day he's out there and he's in this mud pit with pigs, and he's feeding the pigs,

18:19.522 --> 18:22.025
He's realizing, man, these pigs got more food than I do.

18:23.147 --> 18:27.152
And he began to become envious of the food the pigs were eating.

18:27.613 --> 18:29.656
This is as low as you can go.

18:29.776 --> 18:30.697
Has anybody ever been there?

18:32.519 --> 18:34.562
Envious of pig food.

18:37.146 --> 18:42.813
Sometimes Jesus has to let us go and to show us the grass is not greener on the other side.

18:44.275 --> 18:49.522
And so there he is in the mud and he's looking at these pigs and he's tempted to put their food in his mouth and he's like,

18:49.762 --> 18:55.469
Jesus says he comes to his senses and he goes, wait a second, wait a second.

18:56.790 --> 19:01.516
My dad's got all these hired servants back at the house and here's what I'll do.

19:01.556 --> 19:06.561
I'll just get out of this pit and I'll go back to my dad and I'll tell him I don't want to be your son anymore.

19:06.581 --> 19:07.663
I've kind of lost that privilege.

19:07.703 --> 19:13.770
All I want to do is be your hired servant and I'll just go back and I'll have food and I'll have a warm bed.

19:13.970 --> 19:16.653
And so he gets up and he goes home.

19:16.693 --> 19:17.554
Listen to verse 20.

19:18.722 --> 19:20.966
So he returned home to his father.

19:21.126 --> 19:22.128
What does it mean to repent?

19:22.729 --> 19:26.135
Didn't we say it means to turn around, to to acknowledgement?

19:26.315 --> 19:27.597
I'm going the wrong way.

19:27.878 --> 19:29.741
I need to go back to my father.

19:29.801 --> 19:32.185
That's what it means to return.

19:32.225 --> 19:39.277
And by the way, just a little side note, what is the rationale for repentance?

19:40.319 --> 19:44.626
What is the motivation for anyone to repent?

19:48.066 --> 19:51.894
What is the basis for one turning one's life around?

19:51.934 --> 19:57.966
Isn't it the unconditional love and mercy of God?

19:59.729 --> 20:02.815
Isn't it the knowledge that if I go home, my dad will receive me?

20:03.917 --> 20:08.306
I mean, what if this cat, what if this kid thought that, I can't go home?

20:10.018 --> 20:11.380
Man, I know my dad's temper.

20:11.440 --> 20:15.064
I know that if I show up on the porch, he's gonna punish me.

20:15.284 --> 20:16.305
He might even beat me.

20:16.505 --> 20:18.347
He might even make me pay everything back.

20:18.427 --> 20:19.529
I can't pay back.

20:20.149 --> 20:21.771
He might just run me off.

20:22.152 --> 20:23.093
I've insulted him.

20:23.133 --> 20:25.555
I can't go home.

20:25.976 --> 20:27.638
What if that was what he thought about his father?

20:27.678 --> 20:28.399
Would he have gone home?

20:28.439 --> 20:28.839
Yes or no?

20:30.021 --> 20:30.361
No way.

20:31.042 --> 20:34.085
Some of you think that about God.

20:36.047 --> 20:38.450
Some of you have thought about going home and repenting

20:39.202 --> 20:44.369
Getting back in the church and giving your life completely back to God, because you know you're on the wrong path, but you haven't.

20:44.850 --> 20:51.679
And the reason you haven't, listen, is because you're not convinced that if you show up on the porch, he will receive you.

20:52.740 --> 20:53.862
And you are dead wrong.

20:55.464 --> 20:55.925
Let me show you.

20:57.827 --> 20:59.530
So he gets up and he goes back to his dad.

20:59.830 --> 21:06.659
And while he was still a long way off, not even close to home yet, his father saw him coming.

21:06.860 --> 21:08.562
Now why did his father see him coming?

21:09.410 --> 21:10.652
Wasn't his dad on the porch?

21:11.212 --> 21:13.936
Wasn't he pacing back and forth?

21:13.956 --> 21:15.398
Were it his eyes searching their eyes?

21:15.418 --> 21:15.879
And yes or no?

21:16.259 --> 21:16.960
Talk to me.

21:16.980 --> 21:19.464
How is it that his dad saw him when he was still way out there?

21:19.764 --> 21:20.886
It was because his dad was what?

21:21.046 --> 21:22.067
Talk to me.

21:22.087 --> 21:23.469
His dad was looking for him.

21:23.669 --> 21:25.632
His dad was relentlessly pursuing him.

21:25.872 --> 21:27.334
Saying, when's my son going to come home?

21:27.535 --> 21:28.035
Where is he?

21:28.276 --> 21:28.816
I can't wait.

21:29.097 --> 21:30.218
All I want to do is receive him.

21:30.399 --> 21:31.340
I wish he would come home.

21:32.622 --> 21:33.303
And then there he is.

21:33.323 --> 21:33.763
Oh my gosh.

21:33.783 --> 21:34.204
Oh my gosh.

21:34.224 --> 21:34.644
There he is.

21:35.245 --> 21:38.770
And what I'm about to read to you is perhaps the best statement in the entire Bible.

21:39.906 --> 21:43.410
maybe in all of the literature in this entire world.

21:46.854 --> 21:54.083
Filled with love and compassion, he ran to his son.

21:56.126 --> 21:56.666
Picture this.

21:57.768 --> 22:03.154
God, running after sinners.

22:05.794 --> 22:08.438
And when he gets to his son, he embraces him.

22:08.458 --> 22:11.041
And after he embraces him, he starts kissing him.

22:12.383 --> 22:15.868
There is no faith system on this planet other than Christianity.

22:15.908 --> 22:16.428
Listen to me.

22:16.649 --> 22:17.430
You can check it out.

22:17.470 --> 22:18.051
Judaism.

22:18.271 --> 22:19.573
You can check out Hinduism.

22:19.593 --> 22:21.095
You can check out the Muslim faith.

22:21.115 --> 22:24.679
You can look at any faith system, any other religion on this planet.

22:25.120 --> 22:32.530
None of them portray God as a God who runs towards people who said no to him, who turned their back on him.

22:33.890 --> 22:39.877
None of them portray God as a God who would run towards a sinner and hug him and kiss him, except for Christianity.

22:41.439 --> 22:42.921
And that's what the father does.

22:44.422 --> 22:52.252
And in the midst of being squeezed and kissed, he starts to go into his speech, oh, dad, this is awkward.

22:53.053 --> 22:54.755
I'm not worthy to be your son anymore.

22:54.795 --> 22:56.997
I'd like to just be one of the hired servants.

22:57.057 --> 23:00.882
Like, I'm just, you know, and his dad cuts him off.

23:02.210 --> 23:03.712
Doesn't even let him finish his speech.

23:03.752 --> 23:05.175
Listen to what he says to his servants.

23:05.195 --> 23:08.780
He says, quick, bring the finest robe in the house and put it on him.

23:08.800 --> 23:12.065
Get a ring for his finger and a sandals for his feet.

23:12.646 --> 23:15.050
Go get the calf that we've been fattening.

23:15.250 --> 23:15.510
Why?

23:15.851 --> 23:21.479
Because we must say it with me, celebrate with a feast.

23:21.880 --> 23:25.746
This is God's heart for people that have walked away, wandered away.

23:26.882 --> 23:27.923
celebration.

23:28.384 --> 23:31.568
For this son of mine, he was dead and now he's returned to life.

23:31.809 --> 23:33.291
He was lost and now he's found.

23:33.571 --> 23:34.933
And so the what?

23:34.953 --> 23:36.515
The party began.

23:36.535 --> 23:37.717
What?

23:43.064 --> 23:50.254
God wants to throw a party for people who turn around and come back and say, I have blown it.

23:50.394 --> 23:51.295
I have messed up.

23:51.515 --> 23:52.416
I'm so sorry.

23:52.436 --> 23:56.562
I can keep preaching.

23:58.306 --> 24:02.192
But I think it's better not to because sometimes you just need to see it.

24:03.474 --> 24:04.656
You just need to taste it.

24:04.696 --> 24:07.220
You just need to feel it from a real person.

24:09.043 --> 24:13.089
I want you to hear Kaylee's story because it's a story of someone who did this very thing.

24:15.252 --> 24:20.961
Walked away from God, turned around, came back.

24:22.764 --> 24:25.308
That which was out of place was put back into place.

24:25.688 --> 24:26.770
Check out Kaylee's story.

24:29.186 --> 24:34.911
I'm Kaylee Quirk and I've been coming to a manual for two years now.

24:34.931 --> 24:40.937
I found out my mom was diagnosed with breast cancer shortly after I started my freshman year high school.

24:41.578 --> 24:47.363
I already didn't really have a lot of friends and now I was worried about not having a mom.

24:47.924 --> 24:56.712
I kind of just fell into a hole of sadness and depression and didn't really want to participate in making friends or doing well in classes.

24:56.732 --> 24:58.674
I started stealing.

24:58.882 --> 25:01.426
which is what landed me probation.

25:01.486 --> 25:08.295
They told me that I was gonna be emptying trash at a church, but manual was at church.

25:09.818 --> 25:18.129
When I started doing community service here, the lady who was supposed to be my supervisor was not on time and I actually had to sit through service waiting on her.

25:18.149 --> 25:26.962
I remember sitting there and thinking that everyone around me was delusional in that

25:27.682 --> 25:30.687
They were singing and praising something that wasn't real.

25:31.207 --> 25:37.277
Yet when he started talking and giving the message, I felt like he was talking directly to me and I cried the whole time.

25:38.539 --> 25:42.244
I left because I didn't feel like I belonged.

25:42.264 --> 25:48.674
I didn't feel like if I stayed, it was going to make any difference in the damage I had already done in my life.

25:49.355 --> 25:54.002
The choices that I had made, wasn't going to make my mom not sick.

25:54.626 --> 25:58.271
And I felt like if there was a God, he would have taken it away already.

25:59.232 --> 26:09.186
I got to the point where I was so mad and I was angry at God that it affected the way I treated her and my family.

26:09.226 --> 26:18.639
Even after learning my senior year that my mom had actually entered remission, I had already decided that it wasn't for me.

26:19.260 --> 26:20.622
Being a Christ follower wasn't for me.

26:20.642 --> 26:23.506
It put me on a pretty, pretty dark path.

26:24.642 --> 26:37.261
The following four years after I graduated high school and after my mom was in remission, I developed an alcohol problem, a drug problem, and a sex problem.

26:38.623 --> 26:42.369
And it got pretty heavy to the point where I didn't care I was affecting me.

26:42.609 --> 26:44.232
I didn't care I was affecting my family.

26:44.692 --> 26:49.760
I could do whatever I wanted, whatever I wanted, however I wanted, and it was nobody.

26:49.780 --> 26:53.746
There was nobody to hold me accountable for anything until I had to hold myself accountable.

26:54.882 --> 27:05.058
When those decisions led to me getting pregnant with my son, I had to stop doing everything that I thought was important to me at the time.

27:05.759 --> 27:12.189
After leaving all of those bad habits, the people who I thought were my friends and my family kind of left too.

27:12.890 --> 27:13.792
And so I felt alone.

27:13.812 --> 27:15.494
I felt like I didn't have anywhere to go.

27:15.514 --> 27:17.057
I had nobody to talk to.

27:17.077 --> 27:22.866
I wasn't really sure that church would be a good place to go either because I didn't have a

27:23.138 --> 27:26.782
bring on my finger, I didn't have a man with me, and I knew people would be staring.

27:27.863 --> 27:39.717
I didn't have money, I didn't have a place to raise a child, I just messed myself, I didn't know how I was gonna take care of a little human too, I was barely able to take care of myself.

27:41.279 --> 27:51.410
So I just needed to clear my head and went for a drive and drove for a long time, and I actually thought about

27:51.938 --> 27:54.621
just driving off the side of the road quite a few times.

27:54.922 --> 28:02.071
I didn't think that the world needed me and I wasn't equipped to take care of a kid either.

28:02.111 --> 28:10.321
After driving for a while, I ended up in the old parking lot of my childhood church.

28:11.062 --> 28:15.308
It was the first time I'd been in a church since I was doing community service at a manual.

28:16.069 --> 28:20.434
It was kind of the same overwhelming feeling that I had.

28:20.866 --> 28:22.569
when I was listening to Danny talk.

28:23.610 --> 28:30.822
And I just kind of gave up and I asked God what He wanted me to do and what His plan was going forward because I needed help.

28:31.423 --> 28:32.204
God was actually there.

28:32.244 --> 28:42.160
And that was actually trying to reach out to me and following that day I ended up coming back to a manual for the first time in four years.

28:42.901 --> 28:45.605
And it was a much different experience from the first time I stepped foot here.

28:45.625 --> 28:48.850
I felt like I wanted to be there and

28:49.762 --> 28:50.923
I didn't have another option.

28:51.364 --> 28:52.365
My life had to turn around.

28:52.405 --> 29:00.674
All the times that my mom told me to pursue God and to go after God and to go to church and to pray.

29:00.714 --> 29:02.296
And I never did any of it.

29:02.877 --> 29:14.029
But I also didn't pay attention to the little things that God was putting in my life and doing in my life that were showing me that he was actively pursuing me and pursuing a friendship and a relationship with me.

29:14.870 --> 29:18.034
And it's not until now that I noticed those little pieces fit together.

29:19.330 --> 29:22.854
Our family hasn't sat together in a church since I was a little girl.

29:23.795 --> 29:25.736
And now my entire family is part of the church.

29:27.939 --> 29:32.183
I used to make fun of people for praying and worshiping.

29:32.203 --> 29:33.324
I can't not sing now.

29:34.625 --> 29:35.887
I can't not hold my hands up.

29:37.849 --> 29:41.292
Because I know his presence is real.

29:41.312 --> 29:42.133
God did find me.

29:43.995 --> 29:47.058
For a long time I thought that he had given up on me.

29:48.706 --> 29:53.992
But I think no matter where I ran to, he was still there, and he was still chasing after me.

29:55.114 --> 29:56.135
And there was nowhere I could go.

29:56.155 --> 29:59.219
And I'm glad he did find me.

30:15.258 --> 30:18.482
One of my favorite things she said in that video, there's so many good things,

30:20.258 --> 30:24.583
No matter where I went, no matter where I ran to, God was chasing after me.

30:26.224 --> 30:30.889
That is our Father's heart for every single human being on this planet.

30:32.591 --> 30:37.036
You have a cali in your life, don't you?

30:37.196 --> 30:37.637
Yes or no?

30:39.719 --> 30:40.800
You have two, three.

30:41.761 --> 30:49.970
Somebody that you know is on the wrong path, they need to turn into the kingdom of God and find life, grace,

30:50.306 --> 30:51.688
hope, meaning, purpose.

30:52.169 --> 30:53.691
That is what our church is all about.

30:54.832 --> 31:01.942
We are on a relentless pursuit to put that which is out of place, back into place.

31:03.844 --> 31:08.871
If that's your heart, it matches the heart of this church, the mission of this church.

31:10.794 --> 31:15.200
And before Jesus went back to heaven, He died on the cross for our sins.

31:15.941 --> 31:17.042
He came back to life.

31:18.210 --> 31:22.656
Before he left, he said something very clear to his disciples.

31:23.157 --> 31:25.279
John chapter 20 verse 20, I'll never forget this.

31:26.361 --> 31:30.026
I was sitting in a class, a missions class at Liberty University.

31:32.850 --> 31:41.721
And the teacher of that class said, this is the direction for your life, whether you're full-time ministry or average run-of-the-mill Christ follower.

31:42.262 --> 31:44.325
This is the mission of your life.

31:45.707 --> 31:46.668
Jesus gave it to us.

31:46.748 --> 31:48.210
John chapter 20 verse 21.

31:48.706 --> 31:54.793
He said to his disciples, peace be with you, as the Father has sent me into this world to do what?

31:54.833 --> 31:56.916
To put back into place what is out of place.

31:58.197 --> 32:01.621
As the Father has sent me, so now I'm sending whom?

32:03.664 --> 32:03.884
Me.

32:05.746 --> 32:12.434
So sitting in that classroom some 18 years ago, I'm like, oh, I get it.

32:13.474 --> 32:19.546
Like whether I had no plans of becoming a pastor, that wasn't on my to-do list.

32:19.566 --> 32:22.812
I was just a regular guy just trying to learn how to follow Christ.

32:23.093 --> 32:24.315
I'm like, great, that's my mission.

32:24.595 --> 32:26.239
Whatever it is I end up doing with my life.

32:27.461 --> 32:29.304
Jesus has handed the ball off to me.

32:30.447 --> 32:32.210
And now it's my job to kind of

32:32.482 --> 32:33.123
fulfill the mission.

32:33.163 --> 32:36.186
I think it's kind of crazy, Jesus, that you would do that because we're messed up.

32:36.206 --> 32:38.628
People, we're unfaithful people, we're sinful people.

32:38.668 --> 32:41.531
Nevertheless, he says, I'm gonna fulfill the mission through you.

32:41.591 --> 32:44.553
If he were here today, this is what he would say to us.

32:45.474 --> 32:48.577
I am going to put into place what is out of place through you.

32:49.798 --> 32:50.599
A little bit louder.

32:50.639 --> 32:53.001
You, through me, through you.

32:54.883 --> 32:56.945
Like Jesus is not here anymore, have you noticed?

32:58.006 --> 32:59.588
If he were, I'd ask him to give the talk.

32:59.668 --> 33:01.970
That'd be a lot better than me, right?

33:04.098 --> 33:13.729
He says, no, no, I've left and I've given you my spirit and now the ball is in your hands and I want you to relentlessly pursue your friends as the father sent me so I'm sending you.

33:14.310 --> 33:16.032
Who are the calies in your life?

33:18.275 --> 33:20.317
Who are the people that are going the wrong way?

33:20.337 --> 33:25.143
If you're a high school student, you have hundreds of these people in your life.

33:26.404 --> 33:28.927
Middle school student, you have hundreds of these people in your life.

33:29.728 --> 33:31.410
Going down the wrong path.

33:31.714 --> 33:32.936
pursuing the wrong things.

33:32.976 --> 33:36.280
If you work in an office complex, you have hundreds of people in your life.

33:38.163 --> 33:43.170
If you're a teacher, you have coworkers and students all around you that are going down the wrong path.

33:45.974 --> 33:56.589
Wherever you are in your life, there are people around you like Kaylee who are just one invitation away from perhaps turning their entire life around and stepping into the kingdom of God.

33:58.872 --> 34:00.274
And you know, we don't have much time.

34:02.530 --> 34:11.685
If you were listening closely to Kaylee's video, she said when she was on that drive, she thought about driving off the road a few times.

34:12.827 --> 34:14.209
Look, we don't have all the time in the world.

34:14.349 --> 34:15.712
People commit suicide every day.

34:17.815 --> 34:19.698
People die every day of accidents.

34:20.514 --> 34:21.095
tragedies?

34:21.756 --> 34:27.884
We don't have all the time in the world to sit around and be like, oh, well, maybe I'll invite them to church next year.

34:28.505 --> 34:32.591
It's too tense to talk about religion around the Thanksgiving table.

34:33.011 --> 34:34.113
I don't want to bring it up.

34:34.814 --> 34:37.718
We don't have that kind of time.

34:37.898 --> 34:39.661
We don't know how long people are going to live.

34:41.543 --> 34:43.766
And if they should die, it's over.

34:44.547 --> 34:45.388
Game over.

34:46.470 --> 34:47.411
And your notes are like this.

34:47.511 --> 34:49.394
Unless people are found,

34:49.634 --> 34:54.279
They will be out of place forever, forever.

34:55.600 --> 35:00.426
Listen, I wish there was a place called Purgatory, but I've read the book, cover to cover, many, many times.

35:02.007 --> 35:14.160
I wish there was this holding place called Purgatory that if you weren't a Christ follower, you know, people on earth could pray for you and then maybe after a few years or whatever, you could go to heaven after that and maybe not go to the other place.

35:14.601 --> 35:16.223
I wish that were true, but it's not.

35:16.363 --> 35:17.123
It's not in the book.

35:18.965 --> 35:19.506
I've checked.

35:20.898 --> 35:24.843
Once this life is over, your eternal destiny is sealed.

35:25.143 --> 35:26.205
That's the way Jesus taught it.

35:27.166 --> 35:28.968
This life is the only chance we get.

35:29.609 --> 35:30.911
We don't have all the time in the world.

35:32.433 --> 35:33.954
We have to have conversations.

35:33.994 --> 35:39.101
We have to love on people and invite them and help them to turn into the kingdom of God.

35:39.321 --> 35:40.583
So let me ask you a question.

35:40.603 --> 35:42.826
Who are you gonna relentlessly pursue?

35:43.506 --> 35:45.108
Like who are the calies in your life?

35:45.429 --> 35:49.554
Who are those people that are one breath away from being out of place forever?

35:51.362 --> 35:52.985
God wants to use you in their life.

35:54.907 --> 36:07.988
And that's why we as a church have set it up to where, to empower you, to encourage you, to invite them and to bring them to hear the message of the gospel, love, forgiveness, hope, grace, purpose, meaning, peace and joy.

36:08.008 --> 36:12.675
But I can't invite your friends because I don't have proximity.

36:14.277 --> 36:15.139
I'm not in your life.

36:16.962 --> 36:17.943
You must invite them.

36:19.125 --> 36:19.826
You must bring them.

36:21.122 --> 36:23.868
We would love for you right now, as all of our campuses.

36:24.088 --> 36:28.718
We would love for you to think about those people, two, three, four, five people, whoever they are in your life.

36:29.159 --> 36:32.005
And we would love for you to write their names on the boards.

36:32.105 --> 36:34.711
It's okay to write on the walls in church.

36:35.893 --> 36:40.783
No, we actually used to write on stage, but then it looked like graffiti and it just was bad on camera.

36:41.004 --> 36:42.066
But anyway,

36:42.402 --> 36:44.585
We want every single one of you.

36:44.605 --> 36:47.068
We put these name boards all across each campus.

36:47.108 --> 36:47.949
You can see them here.

36:47.989 --> 36:50.252
They're up to here at the Greenwood campus from the balcony.

36:50.272 --> 36:51.193
Why are those there?

36:51.213 --> 37:02.528
Because we want you to write the names down of the people, the Kayleys in your life, that if they're not found in this life, they will spend eternity lost forever.

37:02.548 --> 37:03.890
This is a big deal.

37:04.418 --> 37:24.811
So our band's gonna lead us in a song here, and I wanna encourage you, all of our campuses, every single one of you, if it's just one person in your mind, I would love for you to get out of your seat during this song, and leave, and there's markers back there, there's markers right by the board, and just write their name down, and then say a prayer and say, God, give me the courage to relentlessly pursue this person.

37:25.071 --> 37:29.418
Don't write a famous person, don't write prayers for somebody who's sick, that's not what the boards are for, okay?

37:29.979 --> 37:31.922
They're for people in your life,

37:33.186 --> 37:37.190
that if not found, we'll be out of place forever.

37:37.230 --> 37:37.911
Will you pray with me?

37:40.113 --> 37:50.904
First of all, God, we want to say thank you for pursuing Kaylee, for relentlessly pursuing her through her parents, through circumstances, through friends, to bring her home.

37:52.125 --> 37:55.108
You put a person who was out of place into place.

37:56.289 --> 37:58.532
And so we give, we give you praise for that.

37:59.653 --> 38:00.914
God, right now we ask,

38:01.954 --> 38:07.483
that you would put that person in our lives, on our heart, burden us for them.

38:08.785 --> 38:11.649
They need to turn back into your kingdom.

38:13.152 --> 38:16.737
Give us the courage right now to get out of our seat and get uncomfortable.

38:18.540 --> 38:26.272
Write their names down on the board and begin praying for an opportunity to talk to them, to invite them and to bring them to a service.

38:27.694 --> 38:30.098
We pray this in Christ's name, amen.

38:34.658 --> 38:48.413
The basis for repentance, the motivation for turning back to God, the rationale for returning home is the knowledge of God's unconditional love.

38:48.453 --> 38:49.314
Listen, listen, listen.

38:49.915 --> 38:55.802
When the Father saw the Son a long way off, filled with love and compassion, He ran.

38:55.842 --> 38:58.925
He ran.

38:58.945 --> 39:00.547
Do you understand that?

39:02.309 --> 39:03.410
He didn't walk.

39:04.866 --> 39:06.628
He ran towards the sun.

39:07.328 --> 39:09.751
And when he got to the sun, he grabbed him.

39:10.572 --> 39:12.313
And when he grabbed him, he kissed him.

39:12.353 --> 39:14.576
Do you feel that?

39:15.416 --> 39:16.477
Do you sense that?

39:18.720 --> 39:27.628
The basis for coming home to God is the absolute knowledge and confidence that when you do, he will accept you.

39:27.649 --> 39:29.070
Some of you needed to hear that today.

39:30.071 --> 39:33.234
And some of you need to repent and turn to God.

39:33.538 --> 39:37.762
and find your home in the kingdom and receive forgiveness and grace.

39:37.882 --> 39:39.103
And you know who you are.

39:40.184 --> 39:41.866
You're the calies in the crowd right now.

39:43.147 --> 39:44.228
Some of you are Christians.

39:45.129 --> 39:48.292
You're still, you need to repent and come home.

39:48.312 --> 39:51.115
Some of you are not yet in the kingdom and you need to come home for the first time.

39:51.615 --> 39:55.339
So I'm gonna say a prayer, whoever whichever one you are, I'm gonna say a prayer.

39:55.359 --> 39:56.380
And this is your moment.

39:57.801 --> 39:59.463
The father's been searching the horizon.

39:59.483 --> 40:01.305
He's like, finally she's here.

40:02.005 --> 40:02.866
She's coming.

40:03.234 --> 40:03.875
He's here.

40:03.935 --> 40:06.839
And he's running towards you in this moment.

40:07.539 --> 40:13.547
And he wants to put his arms around you and put a robe on you and shoes for your feet and a ring for your finger.

40:13.767 --> 40:16.310
And he wants to celebrate with the calf.

40:17.412 --> 40:18.353
And he wants to have a party.

40:19.875 --> 40:21.737
If that's you right now, I'm going to say a simple prayer.

40:21.757 --> 40:25.202
Just close your eyes, whatever campus you're at, watch it online here at Greenwood.

40:25.682 --> 40:29.307
This is your moment, the father's waiting.

40:29.327 --> 40:30.448
Come home to him right now.

40:30.488 --> 40:31.890
Say this to him, dear Jesus.

40:33.826 --> 40:34.947
Thank you for loving me.

40:35.588 --> 40:37.149
Thank you for never giving up on me.

40:37.290 --> 40:38.331
I come home now.

40:39.992 --> 40:45.138
I put my trust in you today, your unconditional love and mercy.

40:46.840 --> 40:58.031
Thank you for dying on the cross from my sin, proving your love for me, washing away all my guilt and shame, taking the penalty in my place.

40:59.733 --> 41:00.754
I trust in you today.

41:03.362 --> 41:12.656
I sense and receive your love and compassion, your tender arms around me, your soft kiss on my face.

41:16.021 --> 41:16.682
I'm your child.

41:18.905 --> 41:22.170
It's so good to be home.

41:22.190 --> 41:23.392
I pray this in Christ's name.

41:24.693 --> 41:25.074
Amen.

